text: Sandoval County is a county located in the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 148,834, making it the fourth-most populous county in New Mexico. The county seat is Bernalillo. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:20th-century establishments in New Mexico Territory Category:1903 establishments in the United States
title: Sandoval County, New Mexico
